WEBVTT

00:07.200 --> 00:10.040
[ Dramatic music plays ]

00:21.960 --> 00:24.840
[ Door creaks ]

00:50.520 --> 00:52.800
[ Water splashes ]

00:58.960 --> 01:02.000
[ Theme music plays ]

01:24.840 --> 01:26.680
[ Indistinct conversation,
laughter ]

01:35.080 --> 01:37.360
Perhaps you should slow down?

01:39.920 --> 01:42.200
Fish piss in water, Graham.

01:42.200 --> 01:45.360
So, Lucy, this is
your first time here?

01:47.600 --> 01:51.080
Sadly, stuffy dinner parties
are part of the job.

01:51.080 --> 01:53.480
Though winding up
the Cavendishes is the most fun

01:53.480 --> 01:56.000
to be had with your clothes on.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
Where is Melissa anyway?

01:58.000 --> 02:02.720
I've been honing
my barbed comments all week.

02:02.720 --> 02:04.960
Don't worry, Beryl.

02:04.960 --> 02:06.760
You're not at work now.

02:06.760 --> 02:09.920
You can tell Melissa to bog off
if she annoys you.

02:09.920 --> 02:12.720
I'm not sure I can.

02:12.720 --> 02:16.440
I don't think I've ever told
anyone to bog off.

02:16.440 --> 02:18.400
Well, don't worry, I have,

02:18.400 --> 02:21.680
and I'm only too happy to tell
Melissa what is on my mind.

02:21.680 --> 02:24.880
Jesus, Harry, that hobby horse?

02:24.880 --> 02:26.760
What's this?

02:26.760 --> 02:29.760
Cavendish is trying to cut
the scholarship program.

02:29.760 --> 02:31.680
It's his wife's idea, of course.

02:31.680 --> 02:37.840
Ah, Harry, you came.

02:37.840 --> 02:39.480
And there was me
under the impression

02:39.480 --> 02:40.840
you hadn't been invited,

02:40.840 --> 02:42.840
not being a part
of the faculty anymore.

02:42.840 --> 02:45.600
Clearly an oversight, Lawrence.

02:45.600 --> 02:48.200
I just wanted to spare you
the embarrassment.

02:48.200 --> 02:50.520
How thoughtful.

02:50.520 --> 02:55.200
And, Graham, you brought
your secretary.

02:55.200 --> 02:58.600
My partner, Cavendish.

02:58.600 --> 03:01.760
Of course.

03:01.760 --> 03:04.200
Aren't you two brave.

03:04.200 --> 03:07.200
So, where is Melissa?

03:07.200 --> 03:09.920
She and I have so much
to talk about.

03:09.920 --> 03:13.080
The latest fashion,
where she gets her nails done,

03:13.080 --> 03:18.000
why we can't shoot peasants
just for fun.

03:18.000 --> 03:19.840
Melissa is unwell, actually.

03:19.840 --> 03:22.800
Oh, so she won't be joining us?

03:22.800 --> 03:24.520
LAWRENCE: I'm afraid not.

03:24.520 --> 03:27.520
We're all hearing great things
about Lucy

03:27.520 --> 03:29.720
in your old department, Harry.

03:29.720 --> 03:31.560
It really needed a shake-up.

03:31.560 --> 03:34.400
HARRY: Well, I'm a big fan
of the old guard moving on.

03:34.400 --> 03:36.560
I think they should
make it obligatory.

03:36.560 --> 03:42.880
I suppose, if you find your
old age an impediment, Harry.

03:42.880 --> 03:44.640
Enjoy your meal.

03:44.640 --> 03:46.400
There's nothing too chewy.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.000
[ Chuckles ]

03:51.160 --> 03:54.040
Poor Beryl,
she's so uncomfortable.

03:56.200 --> 03:58.960
What? Sorry, Harry.

03:58.960 --> 04:01.520
I was just thinking about
what he said in there.

04:01.520 --> 04:03.560
To tell you the truth,

04:03.560 --> 04:06.200
I've never lectured
on such a well designed course.

04:06.200 --> 04:08.640
Oh, you don't need
to flatter me.

04:08.640 --> 04:09.920
I've seen your file.

04:09.920 --> 04:12.200
You got the job
for a good reason.

04:12.200 --> 04:14.760
Christ, look at this.

04:14.760 --> 04:17.080
Have you every seen
anything that screams

04:17.080 --> 04:19.000
"I've a tiny penis"
more than that?

04:19.000 --> 04:20.200
It's new.
It was probably that

04:20.200 --> 04:22.880
or a two-seater Porsche.

04:22.880 --> 04:24.480
Christ, you were right.

04:24.480 --> 04:26.760
These dinners are painful.

04:26.760 --> 04:28.680
Why do you still come?

04:28.680 --> 04:30.760
Mischief, Lucy.

04:30.760 --> 04:33.680
I'm a thorn in the side
of the likes of Cavendish,

04:33.680 --> 04:35.280
and long may it last.

04:37.440 --> 04:40.280
[ Dramatic music plays ]

04:45.000 --> 04:46.360
Hm.

04:48.200 --> 04:51.160
I highly recommend it.

04:51.160 --> 04:54.760
Getting up when I want to,
doing what I want to.

04:54.760 --> 04:57.160
Haven't you always?

04:57.160 --> 05:00.240
You are very funny
when I'm drunk.

05:00.240 --> 05:02.280
I suppose it helps you have
your little hobby.

05:02.280 --> 05:05.240
Like old Miss Marple.

05:05.240 --> 05:06.960
No, no, it is fun.

05:06.960 --> 05:09.920
I get to find out
everyone's nasty little secrets.

05:09.920 --> 05:11.600
Sticking your nose in.

05:11.600 --> 05:15.040
So, what is wrong
with Melissa really?

05:16.640 --> 05:18.840
No, don't tell me.

05:18.840 --> 05:21.480
She finally realized
she hasn't got a pulse?

05:21.480 --> 05:23.840
Tell me, Harry, did you ever
solve the mystery

05:23.840 --> 05:25.400
of the missing manners?

05:25.400 --> 05:27.760
It's right up there
with the mystery of people

05:27.760 --> 05:31.600
who are promoted
to the level of incompetence.

05:31.600 --> 05:33.960
Don't you want to go
and check on your wife?

05:33.960 --> 05:37.400
Or are you too busy
checking on your housekeeper?

05:37.400 --> 05:38.680
No, wait a minute.
I think I should go up there

05:38.680 --> 05:40.480
and tell her
that she should come down here

05:40.480 --> 05:41.880
and keep an eye on you.

05:41.880 --> 05:45.360
Melissa isn't here.

05:45.360 --> 05:47.600
You just said that she was ill.

05:47.600 --> 05:49.600
That's none of your business.

05:49.600 --> 05:52.480
[ Harry laughs ]

05:52.480 --> 05:54.680
You need two guard dogs,
Cavendish?

05:54.680 --> 05:57.200
Him and Melissa?

05:57.200 --> 06:01.120
Now, with my old
Miss Marple's head on,

06:01.120 --> 06:04.200
I'm finding this
a trifle suspicious.

06:04.200 --> 06:07.000
I mean, first of all you say
that she's ill

06:07.000 --> 06:08.920
and then you say she's gone.

06:08.920 --> 06:12.240
So which one is it?

06:12.240 --> 06:15.440
Or did you do away with her?

06:15.440 --> 06:16.960
For God's sake!

06:16.960 --> 06:19.480
You won't let it rest, will you?

06:19.480 --> 06:20.960
She's gone.

06:20.960 --> 06:24.960
Vamoose! Imithe! Weg! Disparue!

06:24.960 --> 06:28.600
My wife has left me.

06:28.600 --> 06:30.040
Are you happy now?

06:32.360 --> 06:34.760
I don't --
I don't feel very well.

06:34.760 --> 06:35.920
[ Dramatic music plays ]

06:35.920 --> 06:37.720
[ Gags ]

06:42.720 --> 06:44.440
HARRY: Lucy.

06:44.440 --> 06:47.280
[ All gagging, retching ]

06:50.040 --> 06:51.240
What is it?

06:51.240 --> 06:52.680
He has a heart condition.

06:52.680 --> 06:54.200
I think he's having
a heart attack.

06:54.200 --> 06:55.800
Graham, call an ambulance.

07:03.360 --> 07:05.040
Emergency services, please.

07:19.280 --> 07:22.080
Yeah, well, that's the last
of them leaving.

07:22.080 --> 07:27.000
I feel like that cook on the
Titanic,preserved in alcohol.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.920
FERGUS: You staying there now?

07:28.920 --> 07:31.760
I'm in the middle of nowhere
and I came in Graham's car,

07:31.760 --> 07:34.360
the keys for which are currently
with him in the hospital.

07:34.360 --> 07:35.520
Yes.

07:35.520 --> 07:37.560
Well, that's why I called you.

07:37.560 --> 07:40.600
Make sure that Glenn
picks me up in the morning.

07:40.600 --> 07:43.520
FERGUS: Sure. Was it
a vomiting bug or something?

07:43.520 --> 07:46.440
I don't know, maybe they were
all poisoned.

07:46.440 --> 07:47.840
Aren't you supposed
to be studying?

07:47.840 --> 07:49.880
Don't you have English
on Monday?

07:49.880 --> 07:51.040
FERGUS: Yeah, yeah, okay.

07:51.040 --> 07:52.760
Talk tomorrow.

07:52.760 --> 07:55.600
[ Dramatic music plays ]

08:50.120 --> 08:53.920
Harry, what are you doing here?

08:53.920 --> 08:56.680
Oh, I was at the dinner
last night.

08:56.680 --> 08:58.200
Lost my ride to the back
of an ambulance.

08:58.200 --> 09:00.520
What are you doing here?

09:00.520 --> 09:04.480
Well, it turns out
everybody has E. colipoisoning.

09:04.480 --> 09:07.840
Cavendish is an induced coma,
but if he dies,

09:07.840 --> 09:09.200
then the catering company's

09:09.200 --> 09:11.400
facing a corporate
manslaughter charge.

09:11.400 --> 09:15.160
We're just collecting the
food containers as evidence.

09:15.160 --> 09:17.200
I don't know how you managed
to avoid it, though.

09:17.200 --> 09:18.600
Me either.

09:18.600 --> 09:20.200
I ate everything.

09:20.200 --> 09:21.680
JORDAN: Hm.

09:29.520 --> 09:31.560
Harry says she ate everything.

09:36.680 --> 09:38.440
I didn't drink any water.

09:38.440 --> 09:41.360
Wait, Vicky!

09:41.360 --> 09:42.920
Jordan!

09:58.440 --> 09:59.720
[ Whistles ]

09:59.720 --> 10:02.200
Nice gaf, Harry.

10:02.200 --> 10:04.760
The house has its own
well supply.

10:04.760 --> 10:06.320
We are not on the mains.

10:14.760 --> 10:18.040
[ All gagging ]

10:19.800 --> 10:21.640
I take it back.

10:21.640 --> 10:24.200
That's proper rank, that is.

10:24.200 --> 10:25.920
You lot were drinking that?

10:26.520 --> 10:27.760
HARRY: Oh!

10:27.760 --> 10:29.680
VICKY: Ohh.

10:29.680 --> 10:31.520
HARRY: Christ!

10:31.520 --> 10:33.440
That's Melissa Cavendish.

10:33.440 --> 10:36.200
Oh, dear.

10:36.200 --> 10:38.720
[ Siren wails ]

10:41.960 --> 10:45.600
Harry, you knew Melissa?

10:45.600 --> 10:47.840
Well, she was Cavendish's wife.

10:47.840 --> 10:49.400
We weren't friends.

10:49.400 --> 10:51.200
Who were her friends?

10:51.200 --> 10:52.920
Well, if you could
call them that,

10:52.920 --> 10:54.720
pretty much everyone that was
at the dinner last night.

10:54.720 --> 10:57.360
The college elite.

10:57.360 --> 10:59.920
Right. She have any enemies?

10:59.920 --> 11:01.920
Quite a few, I imagine.

11:01.920 --> 11:04.400
She didn't work for the college,
you understand.

11:04.400 --> 11:08.760
But she did like telling its
employees how to do their job.

11:08.760 --> 11:10.920
What's the husband like?

11:10.920 --> 11:14.720
Arrogant, entitled, unpleasant.

11:14.720 --> 11:16.600
Okay, thanks.

11:16.600 --> 11:18.400
Yeah.

11:18.400 --> 11:20.600
I think they call it
corpse water, Harry.

11:20.600 --> 11:22.680
It's when the feces work
their way out of the cadaver --

11:22.680 --> 11:25.200
Please feel free to shut up.

11:25.200 --> 11:27.480
So, are we investigating, Harry?

11:27.480 --> 11:29.000
Why?

11:29.000 --> 11:33.480
Well, it's pretty bloody obvious
who killed her.

11:33.480 --> 11:36.280
Left him, my backside.

11:36.280 --> 11:37.840
What are you doing here anyway?

11:37.840 --> 11:40.200
Aren't you supposed
to be studying?

11:40.200 --> 11:41.200
It's Saturday.

11:41.200 --> 11:43.360
So? Get in the car.

11:43.360 --> 11:46.720
I'm going to drill you
on your Shakespeare.

11:46.720 --> 11:48.680
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

11:51.880 --> 11:54.280
So should we call the boss?

11:54.280 --> 11:56.200
He's on holidays, Jordan.

11:56.200 --> 11:57.720
I've got this.
It'll be fine.

11:57.720 --> 11:59.280
[ Clears throat ]

11:59.280 --> 12:02.120
[ Dramatic music plays ]

12:36.480 --> 12:37.800
JORDAN: Have we heard back
from the pathologist yet

12:37.800 --> 12:39.760
about time of death?

12:39.760 --> 12:41.040
VICKY: He just e-mailed.

12:41.040 --> 12:42.760
Between the rate
of decomposition

12:42.760 --> 12:44.600
and the water damage,
he can confidently say

12:44.600 --> 12:47.160
that she died a week
before she was found.

12:47.160 --> 12:50.200
Saturday the 11th
between 6:00 and 10:00.

12:50.200 --> 12:52.200
So the husband's alibi
stands up.

12:52.200 --> 12:53.680
VICKY: Same with the staff.

12:56.080 --> 12:59.360
If Melissa only mixed with those
posh ones at the dinner party

12:59.360 --> 13:01.040
and one of them killer her,

13:01.040 --> 13:03.480
why would they go to the house
the following Friday,

13:03.480 --> 13:06.600
knowing that her body
was rotting in that well?

13:06.600 --> 13:08.840
Well, we know intelligent
killers maintain appearances.

13:08.840 --> 13:10.640
They get up, they go to work,

13:10.640 --> 13:13.040
they talk as if the person
they murdered is alive and well.

13:20.520 --> 13:21.920
[ Laughs ]

13:21.920 --> 13:25.120
Yeah, we were
the Diamond Banditos --

13:25.120 --> 13:27.160
Dublin's answer to Duran Duran.

13:27.160 --> 13:28.600
I was going to be
the next Roger Taylor.

13:28.600 --> 13:30.400
Well, what happened?

13:30.400 --> 13:32.240
Well, our lead singer moved
to Canada with his family

13:32.240 --> 13:33.640
and we rehearsed in his garage.

13:33.640 --> 13:35.400
So...

13:35.400 --> 13:37.720
Also, none of the rest
of us could sing.

13:37.720 --> 13:39.480
[ Knock on door ]

13:39.480 --> 13:42.200
Are you expecting someone?

13:42.200 --> 13:45.840
My other lover, Mick Jagger.

13:45.840 --> 13:47.000
You'll have a lot to talk about.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.720
I'll bring him right down.

13:48.720 --> 13:50.600
[ Ray laughs ]

13:53.240 --> 13:54.400
Oh.

13:54.400 --> 13:55.880
We need to talk.

13:55.880 --> 13:57.440
Now's not a good time.

13:57.440 --> 14:01.200
VICKY: I'm afraid I'm going
to have to insist.

14:01.200 --> 14:02.720
Okay, Detective.

14:12.960 --> 14:15.880
How did you know Cavendish
had a heart condition?

14:15.880 --> 14:18.440
It's not common knowledge.

14:18.440 --> 14:21.880
Before I retired, he and I
got into a right squabble

14:21.880 --> 14:24.080
and then Melissa rocked up,
as usual,

14:24.080 --> 14:27.840
and said that he had
a congenital defect

14:27.840 --> 14:30.400
and that I wasn't to upset him.

14:30.400 --> 14:32.360
Bollocks to that.

14:32.360 --> 14:33.760
We heard that you were
unhappy with her

14:33.760 --> 14:36.680
about a scholarship fund.

14:36.680 --> 14:39.520
Harry, why did you go
to the dinner that night?

14:39.520 --> 14:42.200
You don't seem to particularly
like either of them.

14:42.200 --> 14:45.240
None of the alumni
like each other,

14:45.240 --> 14:47.360
but nothing gets
in the way of drinks.

14:47.360 --> 14:48.960
Mm.

14:48.960 --> 14:51.280
So you didn't drink
any of the water that night?

14:51.280 --> 14:53.480
Where are you going with this,
Vicky?

14:53.480 --> 14:56.840
Surely you realize
that Cavendish killed her.

14:56.840 --> 14:58.480
First he said she was ill

14:58.480 --> 15:01.280
and then he said
that she'd left him.

15:01.280 --> 15:03.600
Well, she didn't go very far,
did she?

15:03.600 --> 15:06.200
We found a note from Melissa
saying she was leaving him.

15:06.200 --> 15:07.880
Oh, he probably wrote
that himself.

15:07.880 --> 15:10.200
VICKY: And he has an alibi
for the night she was murdered.

15:10.200 --> 15:12.160
The staff have alibis,
as do the people

15:12.160 --> 15:13.360
Melissa interacted
with the most,

15:13.360 --> 15:15.000
who were pretty much
all at the dinner,

15:15.000 --> 15:17.080
just like you said.

15:17.080 --> 15:20.200
The only person left to ask,
Harry, is you.

15:20.200 --> 15:21.760
Could you tell me what you were
doing the evening

15:21.760 --> 15:23.680
of Saturday the 11th?

15:23.680 --> 15:25.920
Well, I can tell you
what I wasn't doing.

15:25.920 --> 15:27.520
Bumping off Melissa.

15:29.920 --> 15:32.640
[ Dramatic music plays ]

15:32.640 --> 15:34.200
The 11th?

15:38.400 --> 15:44.200
I was plunging my downstairs
loo at home alone.

15:44.200 --> 15:45.680
Good God.

15:45.680 --> 15:48.840
Chasing alibis is like
going down a blind alley.

15:48.840 --> 15:50.840
Why don't you focus
on the motive?

15:50.840 --> 15:53.360
I am thinking of motive, Harry.

15:53.360 --> 15:55.200
You say Melissa Cavendish
was disliked,

15:55.200 --> 15:56.920
but no one else
has told us that.

15:56.920 --> 15:59.000
Well, of course they wouldn't.

15:59.000 --> 16:03.400
What they did tell us
is that you hated her.

16:03.400 --> 16:06.240
We're going to need
to take your fingerprints,

16:06.240 --> 16:07.800
just to rule you out.

16:10.920 --> 16:12.200
Did you hear any of that?

16:12.200 --> 16:15.800
[ Chuckles ]
She's just fishing.

16:15.800 --> 16:17.760
She's panicking that Charlie's
going to come home from holiday,

16:17.760 --> 16:19.680
take the case, and solve it.

16:19.680 --> 16:22.360
Or you will.

16:22.360 --> 16:25.200
Where were you on
the 11th anyway?

16:25.200 --> 16:27.400
Was the evening that memorable?

16:27.400 --> 16:32.280
Charming hotel, the roses,
the Jacuzzi.

16:33.520 --> 16:36.600
Oh, shit!

16:36.600 --> 16:38.520
We can't tell them.

16:38.520 --> 16:40.200
Why don't you just go
and make yourself useful,

16:40.200 --> 16:43.160
since I can't use you
as an alibi?

16:43.160 --> 16:44.920
Fergus is going to be here
in a minute.

16:48.400 --> 16:51.200
To even ask me for an alibi.

16:51.200 --> 16:52.760
Have you tried Charlie?

16:52.760 --> 16:55.240
He's in the bloody valley
with his phone turned off.

16:55.240 --> 16:56.920
So we have to solve it?

16:56.920 --> 17:00.160
No, I have to solve it
while I help you pass your exam.

17:00.160 --> 17:01.680
Read your "Romeo and Juliet."

17:01.680 --> 17:04.000
He loves her, she loves him,
mental families.

17:04.000 --> 17:05.840
Bish bash bosh.

17:05.840 --> 17:08.000
It always comes down to sex.

17:08.000 --> 17:11.200
Sex, love, hatred.

17:11.200 --> 17:14.200
With the Cavendishes,
it could be sex.

17:14.200 --> 17:16.400
Jealousy. An affair?

17:16.400 --> 17:19.280
Oh, so Cavendish is Romeo
and Melissa's Juliet?

17:19.280 --> 17:21.680
Hardly.

17:21.680 --> 17:22.960
Shame you're not doing
"Othello."

17:22.960 --> 17:24.480
Now that would be relevant.

17:24.480 --> 17:25.920
[ Cellphone chimes ]

17:28.920 --> 17:30.360
We've got to go.

17:30.360 --> 17:32.200
Where are we going?

17:32.200 --> 17:33.880
Oh, Harry.

17:33.880 --> 17:36.720
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

17:44.400 --> 17:45.360
HARRY: Wait.

18:13.200 --> 18:15.440
Harry.

18:15.440 --> 18:18.480
They've just told me.

18:18.480 --> 18:21.680
I thought she'd left me.

18:21.680 --> 18:25.200
What are you doing here, anyway?

18:25.200 --> 18:26.680
Ah.

18:26.680 --> 18:29.640
You've come to question me.

18:29.640 --> 18:34.960
Believe me, I wouldn't harm
a hair on my wife's head.

18:34.960 --> 18:37.000
I loved her.

18:37.000 --> 18:39.200
Yet, you thought she'd left you?

18:39.200 --> 18:41.640
We had a silly fight.

18:41.640 --> 18:44.080
I went to Belfast for
a weekend conference

18:44.080 --> 18:46.680
and I came home
and she'd left me an e-mail.

18:46.680 --> 18:48.960
Well, didn't you find that odd?

18:48.960 --> 18:52.240
You know how passionate
Melissa was.

18:52.240 --> 18:55.400
I'd upset her.

18:55.400 --> 18:58.040
Well, fondling the housekeeper
would do that.

18:58.040 --> 18:59.680
Jenny?

18:59.680 --> 19:00.880
Don't be absurd.

19:00.880 --> 19:05.840
It was a -- a stupid row.

19:05.840 --> 19:09.960
I assumed Melissa was off
giving my credit card

19:09.960 --> 19:13.600
a battering in some fancy
hotel, punishing me.

19:13.600 --> 19:16.360
Alone or with someone else?

19:16.360 --> 19:19.200
Melissa wouldn't have an affair.

19:19.200 --> 19:21.240
She was...

19:21.240 --> 19:24.200
Reputation meant
everything to her.

19:24.200 --> 19:26.680
Our reputation as a couple.

19:29.400 --> 19:32.400
I didn't even want to go
to that bloody conference

19:32.400 --> 19:35.360
but she was furious,
ranting and raving about it,

19:35.360 --> 19:38.200
about the college,
me being there too much,

19:38.200 --> 19:40.720
the rumors being too much.

19:40.720 --> 19:43.920
What rumors?

19:43.920 --> 19:46.320
Sketch. The nurse is coming.

19:50.640 --> 19:53.080
Could he have sneaked back
from his conference to kill her?

19:53.080 --> 19:54.840
If he was missing that long
from Belfast,

19:54.840 --> 19:56.400
it would have been noted.

19:56.400 --> 19:58.720
He said something about
rumors at the college.

19:58.720 --> 20:01.600
I need to go back and see
what I can find out.

20:01.600 --> 20:03.440
Anyhow, got to get you home.

20:03.440 --> 20:05.080
Shall I drive you
to school tomorrow?

20:05.080 --> 20:06.360
We can do some
last-minute revisions?

20:06.360 --> 20:08.760
No way.
I'm keeping to my routine.

20:08.760 --> 20:11.600
Red Bull and a Kit Kat
on the bus.

20:11.600 --> 20:14.440
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

20:17.200 --> 20:19.240
-[ Doorbell rings ]
-HARRY: If you get this,

20:19.240 --> 20:22.000
remember that light and shade
is always a crowd pleaser.

20:22.000 --> 20:26.000
Romeo called Juliet the sun
and she calls him

20:26.000 --> 20:28.680
whiter than fresh snow
on a raven's back.

20:33.400 --> 20:35.720
Harriet Wild, I'm arresting you
on suspicion

20:35.720 --> 20:37.440
of the murder
of Melissa Cavendish.

20:37.440 --> 20:38.720
You're not obliged
to say anything

20:38.720 --> 20:40.400
unless you wish to do so,

20:40.400 --> 20:41.920
but anything you do say
will be taking in writing

20:41.920 --> 20:45.240
and may be given in evidence.

20:45.240 --> 20:47.440
Time starts now.

20:47.440 --> 20:50.280
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

21:00.880 --> 21:04.440
So, you've decided not to have
a solicitor present.

21:04.440 --> 21:06.840
I did nothing wrong.
You know this is a farce.

21:06.840 --> 21:10.080
But it is in your best interest
to cooperate.

21:10.080 --> 21:11.960
As I said, the injuries
to Melissa's head

21:11.960 --> 21:15.200
are consistent with the ashtray
we retrieved from her home.

21:15.200 --> 21:16.760
Your fingerprints --

21:16.760 --> 21:19.600
I told you I used it the night
that I stayed there.

21:19.600 --> 21:22.920
And traces of blood
were found on it.

21:22.920 --> 21:26.480
Harry, only your fingerprints
are on the murder weapon.

21:26.480 --> 21:28.120
And that's not all, is it?

21:28.120 --> 21:30.720
You had an acrimonious
relationship with Melissa.

21:30.720 --> 21:33.480
You were the only one who didn't
drink the water that night.

21:33.480 --> 21:35.840
And you say you were home alone
the evening she died.

21:35.840 --> 21:39.200
Harry, is there anything
you'd like to alter

21:39.200 --> 21:40.680
about your statement?

21:40.680 --> 21:42.520
No.

21:43.920 --> 21:46.640
[ Clears throat ]

21:46.640 --> 21:49.520
That's you, driving your car,

21:49.520 --> 21:52.160
not two miles from
the Cavendish home

21:52.160 --> 21:55.440
at 5:45 the evening
of the murder.

21:55.440 --> 21:58.120
The second still is you
driving your car back

21:58.120 --> 22:01.200
at 12:30 AM
the following morning.

22:01.200 --> 22:03.120
Enough time to murder Melissa,

22:03.120 --> 22:07.000
put her body in the well,
and clean up.

22:07.000 --> 22:08.800
I went for a drive.

22:08.800 --> 22:12.720
For seven hours.

22:12.720 --> 22:13.800
HARRY: This is crazy.

22:13.800 --> 22:15.600
Why would I kill her?

22:15.600 --> 22:17.480
And then why would
I clean up and --

22:17.480 --> 22:20.880
and leave my fingerprints
on the murder weapon?

22:20.880 --> 22:23.360
You know I didn't do this.

22:23.360 --> 22:24.880
Then help me.

22:24.880 --> 22:26.600
Tell me why you lied.

22:26.600 --> 22:28.800
[ Sighs ]

22:30.560 --> 22:32.040
RAY: Leave a message
and I'll get back to you.

22:32.040 --> 22:34.760
Ray! Oh!

22:43.200 --> 22:44.720
-[ Bell rings ]
-INVIGILATOR: Time's up.

23:15.400 --> 23:17.120
FERGUS: This is madness.

23:17.120 --> 23:18.760
Why did you lie about
being home that night?

23:18.760 --> 23:20.920
-It's complicated.
-Bloody hell, Harry.

23:20.920 --> 23:22.280
Unless you were out
killing someone else,

23:22.280 --> 23:23.880
just tell them where you were.

23:23.880 --> 23:25.240
If I said who I was with,

23:25.240 --> 23:28.280
it would cause
a lot of trouble, okay?

23:28.280 --> 23:30.480
Look, Vicky knows
I'm not a killer.

23:30.480 --> 23:32.920
I'm not being funny, right,
but you're speaking to

23:32.920 --> 23:35.240
a working-class black kid here,
okay?

23:35.240 --> 23:37.840
You might have a lot of faith
in the system, but I don't.

23:37.840 --> 23:39.600
I mean, she brought you in here,
didn't she?

23:39.600 --> 23:41.920
Look, I know, I know the spot
that I'm in

23:41.920 --> 23:43.200
and I know what I have to do.

23:43.200 --> 23:44.960
I have to solve it.

23:44.960 --> 23:46.600
And how are you going to do that
when you're banged up in here?

23:46.600 --> 23:48.600
I'll figure it out.

23:48.600 --> 23:50.840
Look, I just wanted you to know

23:50.840 --> 23:53.520
that I can't help you
with your exams anymore.

23:53.520 --> 23:55.840
You shouldn't even be here.
You should be studying.

23:55.840 --> 23:59.400
Look, my next exam
isn't until noon tomorrow.

23:59.400 --> 24:01.600
You said you were going to go
to the college, right?

24:01.600 --> 24:03.160
What for?

24:03.160 --> 24:05.480
I'll help until
Charlie gets back.

24:05.480 --> 24:08.400
Okay.

24:08.400 --> 24:11.080
Cavendish said there were
rumors at the college.

24:11.080 --> 24:12.640
Well, professors
won't talk to you,

24:12.640 --> 24:14.840
but maybe you can talk
to the support staff.

24:14.840 --> 24:15.920
And how am I supposed
to do that?

24:15.920 --> 24:18.080
I mean...

24:20.680 --> 24:22.880
I suppose Jordan let you in?

24:22.880 --> 24:24.640
About time, Vicky.

24:24.640 --> 24:26.400
I assume you're going to
let me go now?

24:26.400 --> 24:28.600
Actually, your stay in custody
has been extended.

24:28.600 --> 24:30.960
We're transferring you
to the detention center.

24:30.960 --> 24:32.480
What the hell?

24:32.480 --> 24:34.200
You'll get a bail hearing
tomorrow.

24:34.200 --> 24:35.680
You need to sort a solicitor.

24:38.280 --> 24:40.600
FERGUS: I'll fix it, Harry,
okay?

24:40.600 --> 24:42.200
I'll find out who did it.

24:42.200 --> 24:45.680
[ Dramatic music plays ]

24:45.680 --> 24:47.840
[ Buzzer ]

25:06.960 --> 25:09.600
Come on, up to the desk.
Come on.

25:17.520 --> 25:19.760
Take them.

25:19.760 --> 25:21.760
Come on this way.

25:52.200 --> 25:55.040
[ Dramatic music plays ]

26:17.520 --> 26:19.000
Always thought it'd be Cavendish

26:19.000 --> 26:21.200
who'd get whacked
by somebody's husband.

26:21.200 --> 26:22.360
Dirty dog.

26:22.360 --> 26:24.720
Do you know what he said
to me last week?

26:24.720 --> 26:27.920
That if I got my tits done, the
dean would give me a promotion.

26:27.920 --> 26:30.240
No wonder Carole's
always off sick.

26:30.240 --> 26:32.800
Probably exhausted
from finding new ways

26:32.800 --> 26:35.360
to avoid having to go into his
secret little room with him.

27:02.200 --> 27:04.200
Shit.

27:04.200 --> 27:05.680
Harry.

27:53.520 --> 27:55.440
-[ Tray slams ]
-[ Gasps ]

28:13.040 --> 28:14.480
[ Sniffs ]

28:14.480 --> 28:15.680
[ Groans ]

28:15.680 --> 28:16.840
[ Bowl clatters ]

28:22.600 --> 28:23.720
Have you lost your mind?

28:25.960 --> 28:28.200
With respect, Sir,
moving a charged suspect

28:28.200 --> 28:30.200
to a detention center
is standard procedure,

28:30.200 --> 28:31.280
and there's plenty
of evidence --

28:31.280 --> 28:33.400
She's Charlie's mother.

28:33.400 --> 28:35.960
But I'm doing things
by the book for Charlie.

28:35.960 --> 28:38.560
And you weren't here, so I...

28:38.560 --> 28:40.200
And you think that Charlie's
going to see it like that,

28:40.200 --> 28:42.880
do you?

28:42.880 --> 28:46.400
Sort out a house arrest warrant.

28:46.400 --> 28:48.400
Now!

28:48.400 --> 28:50.240
[ Buzzer ]

28:50.240 --> 28:53.480
[ Door slams ]

28:53.480 --> 28:56.360
[ Sighs ]

28:56.360 --> 28:57.920
Oh!

28:59.720 --> 29:01.200
[ Groans ]

29:01.200 --> 29:04.040
[ Dramatic music plays ]

29:21.680 --> 29:25.040
You're going home,
but not alone.

29:32.560 --> 29:36.520
Charlie, you probably
won't get this but I...

29:39.800 --> 29:42.760
I need you, darling.

29:42.760 --> 29:45.280
I'm -- I'm sure
I'm going to be fine,

29:45.280 --> 29:49.400
but I love you.

29:49.400 --> 29:51.800
And Lola.

29:51.800 --> 29:53.360
And Orla.

29:59.920 --> 30:01.640
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

30:01.640 --> 30:03.440
What bloody use were you?

30:08.400 --> 30:11.240
[ Knock on door ]

30:14.360 --> 30:15.680
Oh.

30:15.680 --> 30:18.640
He said we were
going to the cinema.

30:18.640 --> 30:20.680
Well, this is a special edition

30:20.680 --> 30:22.760
of "The Shawshank Redemption,"
darling.

30:22.760 --> 30:25.720
I still can't believe it.

30:25.720 --> 30:27.120
Were you alright?

30:27.120 --> 30:29.880
Well, at least
I didn't get shivved.

30:29.880 --> 30:32.200
Your exams?
I have not forgotten.

30:32.200 --> 30:33.640
FERGUS: Forget about that.

30:33.640 --> 30:36.080
Look, I've actually got
to get her dinner, so...

30:41.080 --> 30:42.360
You do realize you've only got

30:42.360 --> 30:45.920
lobster and wine
in your fridge, right?

30:45.920 --> 30:48.920
Don't you have any, like,
spaghetti hoops or something?

30:49.960 --> 30:52.040
Uh...

30:58.520 --> 31:01.760
So, you find out anything
at the college?

31:01.760 --> 31:03.960
FERGUS: Yeah, I did.

31:03.960 --> 31:05.520
Check this out.

31:09.080 --> 31:11.400
-That's in Cavendish's office?
-Yep.

31:11.400 --> 31:12.920
Oh, probably claims
it's some place for him

31:12.920 --> 31:15.640
to rest his head
at the end of the day.

31:15.640 --> 31:18.280
What are you two talking about?

31:18.280 --> 31:20.720
Never you mind, Stinker.

31:20.720 --> 31:24.920
Here, look, sit down and go
and eat your stuff.

31:27.840 --> 31:30.200
We're talking about
some proper nasty

31:30.200 --> 31:32.840
Harvey Weinstein shit here.

31:32.840 --> 31:35.200
I mean, did you never have
any suspicions about him?

31:35.200 --> 31:36.240
You worked with the guy.

31:36.240 --> 31:38.440
It was a different department.

31:38.440 --> 31:41.960
He probably had some strategy
to keep it quiet.

31:41.960 --> 31:45.600
Maybe even got worse.

31:45.600 --> 31:49.960
He might have just targeted
secretaries or...

31:49.960 --> 31:53.200
or newbies.

31:53.200 --> 31:54.640
Well, it was risky of you
to come here.

31:54.640 --> 31:56.200
We could have talked
on the phone.

31:56.200 --> 31:58.640
Rubbish. I was coming anyway.

31:58.640 --> 32:00.440
I know you didn't kill Melissa.

32:00.440 --> 32:02.800
As for Cavendish...

32:02.800 --> 32:05.760
I just thought you being new,
he might have tried something.

32:05.760 --> 32:09.520
I mean, did he ever mention
his little room?

32:09.520 --> 32:10.760
Hinted.

32:10.760 --> 32:12.200
I told him where to go.

32:12.200 --> 32:14.600
Christ, I had no idea.

32:14.600 --> 32:16.160
You must have been
so uncomfortable

32:16.160 --> 32:18.200
that night at his house,
the party?

32:18.200 --> 32:21.400
I learned long ago how to deal
with men like him.

32:21.400 --> 32:22.920
I would have turned his balls
into a key ring

32:22.920 --> 32:24.920
if he'd done it to me.

32:24.920 --> 32:27.160
But obviously he's been
harassing others.

32:27.160 --> 32:30.400
I hate that men still get away
with shit like this.

32:30.400 --> 32:31.920
If women would just stand up!

32:31.920 --> 32:35.840
It can't be a woman's job
to stop them, Lucy.

32:35.840 --> 32:37.360
People like him are protected.

32:37.360 --> 32:39.200
I mean, you saw the butler.

32:39.200 --> 32:40.800
And the old guard
at the college,

32:40.800 --> 32:42.040
well, they're no better.

32:44.960 --> 32:46.960
Did you notice
how tense Beryl was

32:46.960 --> 32:48.960
when she was around Cavendish?

32:48.960 --> 32:50.520
Really?

32:53.560 --> 32:55.360
Yes, Graham.

32:55.360 --> 32:57.400
Actually in prison.

32:57.400 --> 33:00.200
I can cross off doing bird
from my bucket list.

33:00.200 --> 33:01.920
Anyway, forget about that.

33:01.920 --> 33:04.680
I need to know,
did you ever hear anything,

33:04.680 --> 33:07.720
any rumors about Cavendish
being a predator?

33:07.720 --> 33:10.200
I mean, is it common knowledge?
Bollocks.

33:10.200 --> 33:13.880
Is it common knowledge bollocks?
What?

33:13.880 --> 33:15.840
Just never mind.

33:15.840 --> 33:18.200
Did you know about Cavendish?

33:18.200 --> 33:20.200
GRAHAM: Of course I didn't know.

33:20.200 --> 33:22.480
I mean, I'd heard the odd thing,

33:22.480 --> 33:25.400
but I didn't think
it was anything serious.

33:25.400 --> 33:27.120
You know what it's like
these days.

33:27.120 --> 33:30.720
Smile at somebody and the
woke brigade are all over you.

33:30.720 --> 33:33.600
Myself and Beryl went through
the mill when we were courting.

33:33.600 --> 33:37.000
I had to fill in a rake
of bloody HR forms.

33:37.000 --> 33:39.000
HARRY: Is Beryl there, actually?

33:39.000 --> 33:40.680
Well, she's around.

33:40.680 --> 33:42.960
Oh, there you are.

33:42.960 --> 33:44.800
The Guards arrested Harry.

33:44.800 --> 33:46.000
What?

33:46.000 --> 33:47.600
Oh, God.

33:47.600 --> 33:48.880
That's awful.

33:48.880 --> 33:50.600
No, it's alright, Beryl.
I'm out now.

33:50.600 --> 33:52.720
I just wanted to know,
did you ever hear anything

33:52.720 --> 33:54.680
about Cavendish's wicked ways?

33:54.680 --> 33:56.400
It seems that quite a few
of his secretaries

33:56.400 --> 33:58.360
had run-ins with him
in his little room.

33:58.360 --> 34:00.160
[ Crying ]

34:03.280 --> 34:04.840
What on earth was that about?

34:06.880 --> 34:08.760
Graham, do you think...

34:08.760 --> 34:12.280
Did Beryl ever mention
Cavendish in that way?

34:12.280 --> 34:14.400
Good God.

34:14.400 --> 34:16.400
What are you talking about?

34:16.400 --> 34:18.240
-You don't think...
-I don't know.

34:18.240 --> 34:20.920
[ Knock on door ]

34:20.920 --> 34:22.360
I'm going to have to
call you back.

34:22.360 --> 34:23.920
Go, check on Beryl.

34:27.400 --> 34:28.920
Ma?

34:28.920 --> 34:30.840
Oh!

34:30.840 --> 34:33.760
We were so worried about you.

34:33.760 --> 34:35.080
You got my message?

34:35.080 --> 34:37.400
Yeah, yours, Fergus's, Ray's.

34:37.400 --> 34:39.520
Even the one where you said
you loved Orla.

34:39.520 --> 34:41.200
Are you okay, Harry?

34:47.240 --> 34:49.200
I want the charges
dropped right now.

34:49.200 --> 34:51.280
We can't drop the charges
because you say.

34:51.280 --> 34:52.840
If she's not telling us
where she was

34:52.840 --> 34:55.080
when Melissa was killed,
it's for good reason.

34:55.080 --> 34:56.200
We need to find
the actual killer.

34:56.200 --> 34:57.760
Charlie, you can't
investigate this.

34:57.760 --> 34:59.480
She's your family.

34:59.480 --> 35:01.520
And where were you?

35:01.520 --> 35:03.760
-Why didn't you step in?
-I was on a strategy day.

35:03.760 --> 35:07.040
Look, Charlie, I know
that she didn't do this.

35:09.240 --> 35:10.800
And the --

35:13.880 --> 35:15.520
[ Door slams ]

35:17.880 --> 35:18.920
Right, look --

35:18.920 --> 35:20.280
No, you look.

35:20.280 --> 35:22.200
Okay, I know that
the only reason

35:22.200 --> 35:23.440
why you're bringing me along

35:23.440 --> 35:25.240
is because
Harry nagged you into it.

35:25.240 --> 35:26.520
But the thing is, right,

35:26.520 --> 35:27.880
I'm going to keep
trying to help her,

35:27.880 --> 35:28.800
with or without you.

35:28.800 --> 35:30.200
And from what she says,

35:30.200 --> 35:33.000
you shouldn't be
investigating either.

35:33.000 --> 35:35.640
She shouldn't have told you
that, but fair point.

35:35.640 --> 35:37.440
Alright.

35:37.440 --> 35:39.840
Now, she suspects that Cavendish
harassed that Beryl one.

35:39.840 --> 35:42.160
But she has an alibi,
like all the others.

35:42.160 --> 35:44.400
Vicky's a good cop,
but alibis can be faked.

35:44.400 --> 35:45.840
That's what Harry says,

35:45.840 --> 35:48.920
and she reckons
there are more victims.

35:48.920 --> 35:50.640
Right, tell me everything.

35:50.640 --> 35:53.480
[ Dramatic music plays ]

35:59.920 --> 36:02.960
[ Doorbell rings ]

36:06.440 --> 36:07.840
CHARLIE: Jenny, isn't it?

36:07.840 --> 36:09.200
I need to ask you
some questions.

36:09.200 --> 36:10.400
I can't. Please.

36:10.400 --> 36:12.160
The night of the dinner party,

36:12.160 --> 36:14.680
a witness saw you and Cavendish
in an intimate situation.

36:14.680 --> 36:17.000
What?

36:17.000 --> 36:19.640
No! Whatever you think,
it wasn't like that.

36:19.640 --> 36:22.200
Then why don't you tell me
what it was?

36:22.200 --> 36:24.960
I can't.

36:24.960 --> 36:26.720
It's not --

36:26.720 --> 36:29.040
CHARLIE: Are you scared?

36:29.040 --> 36:30.800
Did you snap, Jenny?

36:30.800 --> 36:32.360
Did you think enough?

36:32.360 --> 36:34.040
Except Cavendish wasn't here,
only his wife?

36:34.040 --> 36:37.440
I wasn't here that night.

36:37.440 --> 36:40.200
And Melissa, she...

36:40.200 --> 36:43.880
Look, my friend, she's getting
blamed for this, okay?

36:43.880 --> 36:45.240
And she didn't do it, okay?

36:45.240 --> 36:48.480
So please help.

36:48.480 --> 36:52.360
Look, this is my job.

36:52.360 --> 36:54.200
If you want to know
what Cavendish is like,

36:54.200 --> 36:55.600
look into the Saturday Club.

36:55.600 --> 36:57.200
Saturday Club? What's that?

36:57.200 --> 36:59.840
What is going on here?

36:59.840 --> 37:03.240
FERGUS: Just think I left
my coat here the other day.

37:03.240 --> 37:06.240
Mind if I have
a quick look around?

37:06.240 --> 37:07.920
Get back to work, Jenny.

37:10.160 --> 37:11.880
You did not leave
your coat here.

37:11.880 --> 37:13.520
I would have found it.

37:13.520 --> 37:15.080
Good day.

37:18.280 --> 37:19.840
He's fun.

37:22.400 --> 37:24.720
So Charlie is going to
double check all the alibis

37:24.720 --> 37:26.200
and he's going to see
what he can find out

37:26.200 --> 37:28.560
about the Saturday Club.

37:28.560 --> 37:30.680
A Saturday Club?

37:39.040 --> 37:43.480
[ Cellphone rings ]

37:43.480 --> 37:44.960
Harry?

37:44.960 --> 37:46.960
Listen, sorry,
I-I need your help again.

37:46.960 --> 37:49.640
Have you ever heard anything
about the Saturday Club?

37:49.640 --> 37:51.400
Is this something
that Cavendish is into,

37:51.400 --> 37:53.160
some sort of man club
or something?

37:53.160 --> 37:55.600
I don't know what clubs
Cavendish is in.

37:55.600 --> 37:57.640
I don't know him that well.

37:57.640 --> 38:00.560
And I tell you, after speaking
with Beryl after you called,

38:00.560 --> 38:02.600
they better keep
that bloody man in hospital,

38:02.600 --> 38:04.200
or I'll put him back in there.

38:04.200 --> 38:06.280
Ah, okay.

38:06.280 --> 38:09.040
Can we speak to Beryl?

38:09.040 --> 38:10.920
She just left.

38:10.920 --> 38:13.200
She's gone to
her women's group.

38:13.200 --> 38:14.960
What women's group?

38:14.960 --> 38:18.000
[ Dramatic music plays ]

38:22.600 --> 38:24.520
Told you Malky
would know someone.

38:24.520 --> 38:26.520
The gift that keeps on giving,
your father.

38:29.400 --> 38:31.520
Saturday night, it'll be
a busy one for him.

38:43.840 --> 38:46.080
6:00 till 8:00,
how to kill predators.

38:46.080 --> 38:48.400
8:00 till 9:00, choir practice.

38:48.400 --> 38:49.960
Shh.

38:56.720 --> 38:59.960
BERYL: I'm done discussing this.

38:59.960 --> 39:02.880
Harry Wild is a good woman.

39:02.880 --> 39:04.760
We need to go to the Guards.

39:04.760 --> 39:06.760
SECRETARY:
But then everything comes out.

39:06.760 --> 39:07.880
I have said it from the start.

39:07.880 --> 39:09.400
I'm glad we came together,

39:09.400 --> 39:13.720
but I don't want my dirty linen
aired in public.

39:13.720 --> 39:16.600
And it's not just
fear of losing our jobs

39:16.600 --> 39:18.520
or people not believing us.

39:21.000 --> 39:23.760
It's about people knowing.

39:23.760 --> 39:26.200
I agree with you.

39:26.200 --> 39:28.240
A-And I'm happy Melissa is dead

39:28.240 --> 39:31.080
so at least she's not
hanging over us anymore.

39:31.080 --> 39:32.720
SECRETARY: I mean, what kind of
an evil bitch

39:32.720 --> 39:33.720
protects her husband like that?

39:33.720 --> 39:36.760
But we can't be false alibis.

39:36.760 --> 39:39.960
We know Lucy wasn't here.

39:39.960 --> 39:42.400
Look, ladies, when she
brought us all together,

39:42.400 --> 39:44.440
she told us if we couldn't
find the courage

39:44.440 --> 39:49.400
to report the Cavendishes,
then she'd do something.

39:49.400 --> 39:51.600
But what if she did?

39:51.600 --> 39:53.680
Lucy?

39:53.680 --> 39:58.000
So Melissa blackmailed them into
keeping quiet, right, but how?

39:58.000 --> 40:01.520
Oh, it's easy, Fergus.
You heard them.

40:01.520 --> 40:03.440
They were probably already
blaming themselves

40:03.440 --> 40:05.840
for being assaulted.

40:05.840 --> 40:07.600
That's how predators work.

40:11.360 --> 40:12.920
Shame is their weapon.

40:15.840 --> 40:17.440
What do you know about Lucy?

40:17.440 --> 40:20.200
I mean, you helped hire her
for your old job, right?

40:20.200 --> 40:21.200
I mean,
where does she come from?

40:21.200 --> 40:22.680
Well, she had a good CV.

40:22.680 --> 40:25.480
A couple of steady
lecture posts.

40:25.480 --> 40:27.680
There was only one blip.

40:27.680 --> 40:29.880
She left her first college
in the middle of a course,

40:29.880 --> 40:31.600
but that's not uncommon.

40:31.600 --> 40:33.360
Wait, she just dropped out?

40:33.360 --> 40:34.920
Where was that?

40:34.920 --> 40:37.080
Galway, about 12 years ago.

40:40.080 --> 40:45.080
She knew that the sculpture
in Cavendish's hall was new.

40:45.080 --> 40:48.800
How, if that was
her first time there?

40:48.800 --> 40:50.760
Holy shit!

40:50.760 --> 40:52.480
HARRY: What?
What have you found?

40:52.480 --> 40:54.720
Nothing about Lucy,
but there is a story here

40:54.720 --> 40:57.400
about a professor
from Galway Uni

40:57.400 --> 41:02.400
who was had up on a rape charge
at around the same time.

41:02.400 --> 41:06.200
Prosecution called the man
a serial predator.

41:06.200 --> 41:08.360
They reckon he'd targeted
more than

41:08.360 --> 41:10.080
just the student
who accused him.

41:11.280 --> 41:14.120
[ Dramatic music plays ]

41:41.000 --> 41:42.760
Is that meant to
wash these down?

41:52.880 --> 41:54.440
Lucy, this isn't the way.

41:56.680 --> 41:58.040
LUCY: I'm sorry, Harry.

42:00.680 --> 42:02.120
I won't let you take the blame.

42:05.200 --> 42:06.880
[ Sighs ]

42:06.880 --> 42:09.440
What choice do I have?

42:09.440 --> 42:12.640
Can't go to prison.

42:12.640 --> 42:15.040
Cavendish hurt so many of us,
you know.

42:17.200 --> 42:20.760
When I found that out, I thought
he can't get away with it.

42:20.760 --> 42:22.960
He can't deny all of us.

42:22.960 --> 42:24.360
I brought us all together.

42:24.360 --> 42:27.840
Thought we could plan
how to bring him down.

42:27.840 --> 42:29.960
But they were terrified.

42:29.960 --> 42:31.840
They saw it more
as a support group.

42:34.440 --> 42:36.480
Did this happen to you before?

42:36.480 --> 42:38.240
You know about that?

42:41.960 --> 42:44.600
It was a lecturer.

42:44.600 --> 42:47.160
I wasn't the only one.

42:47.160 --> 42:48.440
There was one girl,
she was brave enough

42:48.440 --> 42:51.000
to take it to the Guards.

42:51.000 --> 42:54.840
His defense team claimed
she was drunk and consented

42:54.840 --> 42:57.960
and he got away with it.

42:57.960 --> 43:02.680
My mum sat on my bed
every night just to make sure

43:02.680 --> 43:04.840
I didn't slit my wrists
as she slept.

43:07.760 --> 43:09.320
You were very brave.

43:11.480 --> 43:15.880
I can't imagine what it took
for you to --

43:15.880 --> 43:18.440
to try to confront Cavendish.

43:18.440 --> 43:20.720
Look at where it got me.

43:20.720 --> 43:23.760
Stand up to the bullies,
they say.

43:23.760 --> 43:26.440
They'll back down.

43:26.440 --> 43:28.840
But Melissa didn't.

43:28.840 --> 43:31.880
She started ranting about
how she was sick of it,

43:31.880 --> 43:34.360
how she wouldn't be
tainted by rumors.

43:34.360 --> 43:35.840
It was like she was at the end
of her tether

43:35.840 --> 43:37.520
and I was the touch paper.

43:37.520 --> 43:41.720
She got so angry, I thought
she was going to kill me.

43:41.720 --> 43:44.440
-I grabbed what I could.
-The ashtray.

43:44.440 --> 43:47.440
I was just defending myself,
but she collapsed on the spot.

43:47.440 --> 43:49.440
I panicked.

43:49.440 --> 43:53.200
But then I thought
I can cover this up.

43:53.200 --> 43:54.960
Send an e-mail
from her computer,

43:54.960 --> 43:56.040
make it look like she left.

43:58.360 --> 44:02.200
Why on earth did you
drink the water?

44:02.200 --> 44:05.400
I didn't know it was
for the house.

44:05.400 --> 44:07.040
I thought they got their water
from the mains,

44:07.040 --> 44:08.760
like normal people.

44:08.760 --> 44:11.600
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

44:14.720 --> 44:16.560
Charlie.

44:16.560 --> 44:18.000
CHARLIE: Mum,
I think I have something.

44:18.000 --> 44:20.160
The alibis for Beryl Lane
and Lucy D'arcy

44:20.160 --> 44:22.760
are the same,
and they both mention a club.

44:22.760 --> 44:26.200
I'm on my way
to interview Lucy now.

44:26.200 --> 44:27.680
Charlie...

44:31.480 --> 44:33.760
Okay.

44:33.760 --> 44:35.840
[ Crying ]

44:35.840 --> 44:38.680
[ Somber music plays ]

45:07.480 --> 45:10.960
She still killed her, Harry.

45:10.960 --> 45:12.360
Look at how she was provoked.

45:15.480 --> 45:18.600
No.

45:18.600 --> 45:23.200
I won't be responsible
for helping send her to jail.

45:23.200 --> 45:27.400
Trust me.
She'd be dead in 24 hours,

45:27.400 --> 45:31.640
by her own hand
or somebody else's.

45:31.640 --> 45:34.480
[ Somber music plays ]

46:15.680 --> 46:18.720
Lawrence Cavendish,
I'm arresting you on suspicion

46:18.720 --> 46:20.600
of multiple counts
of sexual assault.

46:20.600 --> 46:21.760
You are not obliged
to say anything

46:21.760 --> 46:23.720
unless you wish to do so,

46:23.720 --> 46:26.040
but anything you do say
will be taken down in writing

46:26.040 --> 46:27.680
and may be given in evidence.

46:57.000 --> 47:00.280
I'm not even going to ask.

47:00.280 --> 47:03.160
Probably best.

47:03.160 --> 47:06.480
Harry, I need you to know
that I was ready to confess.

47:06.480 --> 47:10.000
I know full well
what you did for me.

47:10.000 --> 47:12.400
What can I do to make it up?

47:12.400 --> 47:14.880
You can pour me
a glass of champagne...

47:14.880 --> 47:16.240
on your way out.

47:16.240 --> 47:17.520
But I --

47:17.520 --> 47:20.080
Fergus and his sister
are coming over.

47:20.080 --> 47:22.760
He's been working his ass off
to help me

47:22.760 --> 47:24.800
while sitting his Junior Cert.

47:24.800 --> 47:28.800
Ah, he's a good kid.

47:28.800 --> 47:30.360
Yeah.

47:33.960 --> 47:38.680
So, am I forgiven?

47:45.400 --> 47:47.400
I'll think about it.

47:47.400 --> 47:50.240
[ Theme music plays ]
